	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			This is one of the most frustrating quests in Everquest. Yes, you read that correctly. There are three items you need. Two are of no real difficulty, the third is nearly impossible.<BR>
<BR>
The first item is an enchanted platinum bar. You will need an enchanted bar to convert it to Galvanized in the Temple of Solusek Ro. This is not difficult and platinum bars are just money.<BR>
<BR>
The second item is found at the bottom of the river in Everfrost Peaks. You will need Enduring Breath to get the item or you will drown, the location is far from the nearest opening. Bring an Enchanter or Shaman friend. Despite this trouble, this is an easy item to get, it just takes some time.<BR>
<BR>
The final item is dropped by an approximately 30th level Necromancer named Babbinsbort. He spawns on the third level of Befallen. As you enter the third level of Befallen (the door you use the no rent key on) go down the corridor, take the first left, go across the room through the blocked passage and then take a left into another room. This room has a fallen pillar in it. On the side of the pillar away from the door is a spawn point. This spawn point pops every 7 to 8 hours and is the one that Babbinsbort comes from. The length of the spawn is bad enough, but usually it is not the Gnome but a placeholder. I gated into Befallen for 7 straight spawns of that location and saw a rat three twices, a skeleton, and a ghoul twice. This after camping that spot for more than seven hours to time the spawn length. I still have yet to see Babbinsbort and have given up on this quest.<BR>
<BR>
Hope all you other clerics have better luck.
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
									
